  <p>
    <strong>C#</strong> is pronounced as "C-Sharp". It is a modern, versatile, and object-oriented programming language that was developed and created by Microsoft in the year 2000 as a part of the .Net Framework. The C# programming language enables developers to create applications for multiple platforms, such as Windows, macOS, and Linux. It also shares several similarities with other widely-utilized programming languages, such as C++ and Java.
  </p>

